body:
@keith-turner the current version up on github is missing the offending code. If you add the following lines to testSetPropertiesAndGroups() around line 182 it will cause the failure.

```
      if (property.getKey().contains("prop1")) {
        assertEquals(property.getValue(), "val1");
        count++;
      }
      if (property.getKey().contains("prop2")) {
        assertEquals(property.getValue(), "val2");
        count++;
      }
    }
    assertEquals(4, count); 
```

@jmark99 now I see the problem, but I think you may have exposed a bug in your test (which is great).  I doubt this bug has anything to do with your changes, it probably pre-existing.  I suspected the props were not showing up because they lacked the `table.` prefix and therefore were not table properties.  So I added the following and then your test worked.

```
    props.put(Property.TABLE_ARBITRARY_PROP_PREFIX.getKey()+"prop1", "val1");
    props.put(Property.TABLE_ARBITRARY_PROP_PREFIX.getKey()+"prop2", "val2");
```

So what happened when you set the properties without the `table.` prefix?  Were they just silently dropped or was something actually set in zookeeper?  Seems like something should throw an exception when its not a valid table prop.  Could add some sanity checks to NewTableConfiguration in order to fail fast.  May want sanity checks on the server side where create table is processed also.  This could be done as a follow on issue.
